\f1\b XP-58 already paired
\f0\b0  inside RawBT (as you were doing earlier).\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 No extra permissions needed in your app beyond normal ones.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 This works even if your app is from Google Play \'97 it\'92s just standard Android inter-app communication.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 2. Alternative: Install \'93Server for RawBT\'94 + use local TCP port 9100\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 If you prefer socket-based sending (e.g. for easier cross-platform code later), install the free 
\f1\b Server for RawBT
\f0\b0  companion app on the same tablet. It runs a local raw TCP server on 
\f1\b port 9100
\f0\b0 .\
Your app can then open a socket to 
\fs30 127.0.0.1:9100
\fs26  (localhost) and send the exact same byte array above. This is also fully local and works fine from a Google Play app on the tablet.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

